The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 28 January is 187,389 (21,597.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 23 January, there were 9,466 new confirmed cases (1,091.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 January, there were 7,465 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 27% (2,001 extra cases).
